article.headline: Cal St. Fullerton 98, UC Riverside 58
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. (AP) -- Justin Burns had 19 points and 14 rebounds as Cal St. Fullerton beat UC Riverside 98-58 Saturday night. Burns went 9-for-11 from the field to lead the Titans (13-3, 4-1 Big West Conference) to their eighth win in nine games. Marcus Crenshaw had 17 points, Frank Robinson had 14 points and nine rebounds and Bobby Brown had 14 points and 10 assists for Cal State Fullerton. The 40-point victory margin was the largest over a conference opponent in Fullerton history. Chris Johnson led UC Riverside (3-15, 0-5) with 19 points. The Highlanders have lost 13 straight. Their last victory was on Nov. 18 victory over Hope International. Scott Cutley added a third double-double for Fullerton with 10 points and 13 rebounds. The Titans have won 13 straight home games.
